<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/ce0b42642a824fcef71f80629e936107.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 3 and A = 20 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.2</li><li>8.8</li><li>70.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({20}\right)}}}=\frac{{3}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{3}}{{\tan{{\left({20}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{8.2424322583639}\approx{8.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{8.2424322583639}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}+{67.937689533717}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={76.937689533717}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{76.937689533717}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.7714132004893}\approx{8.8}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{20}^{\circ}\approx{70}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

